  </section>

  <section class="signal-strip" aria-label="Research signals">
    <div><strong>AI4EDA</strong><span>learning-based design automation</span></div>
    <div><strong>3D IC</strong><span>early-stage prediction and optimization</span></div>
    <div><strong>DFT</strong><span>fault simulation and functional safety</span></div>
    <div><strong>Builder</strong><span>systems-minded, collaborative, and practical</span></div>
  </section>

  <section id="about" class="section two-col">
    <div>
      <p class="section-kicker">About</p>
      <h2>Careful research, practical systems, and a strong instinct for useful tools.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="rich-text">
      <p>
        My research sits at the intersection of machine learning and electronic design automation. I am interested in building circuit foundation data, representation models, and prediction engines that understand circuits across RTL, netlist, physical layout, timing, power, and verification signals.
      </p>
      <p>
        I also have substantial experience in fault simulation acceleration, functional safety analysis, and commercial EDA tool development. I enjoy research that is mathematically grounded, implementation-ready, and close enough to real chip-design constraints to be useful.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section compact design-dna">
    <div class="dna-item">
      <span>01</span>
      <h3>Think across design stages</h3>
      <p>From RTL and netlists to physical layout, timing, power, and fault behavior.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="dna-item">
      <span>02</span>
      <h3>Build before claiming</h3>
      <p>Algorithms should become measurable systems, not only elegant diagrams.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="dna-item">
      <span>03</span>
      <h3>Collaborate with purpose</h3>
      <p>I value careful communication, shared ownership, and research that can move tools forward.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="research" class="section">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="section-kicker">Research Focus</p>
      <h2>Efficient intelligence for circuit design and validation</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="focus-grid">
      <article class="focus-card">
        <img src="assets/img/icon-repr.svg" alt="" />
        <h3>Multi-Modal Circuit Understanding</h3>
        <p>Datasets, graph learning, and neural representations that connect specifications, RTL, netlists, physical layouts, and performance metrics.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="focus-card">
        <img src="assets/img/icon-timing.svg" alt="" />
        <h3>Timing, Power, and 3D IC Prediction</h3>
        <p>Cross-stage knowledge distillation and learning-based models for early timing and power estimation, including AI-driven 3D IC design automation.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="focus-card">
        <img src="assets/img/icon-fault.svg" alt="" />
        <h3>Fault Simulation and Functional Safety</h3>
        <p>Scalable simulation frameworks for deterministic patterns, transition faults, sequential circuits, and ISO 26262-oriented safety analysis.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="news" class="section compact">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="section-kicker">News</p>
      <h2>Recent Highlights</h2>
