  <section id="collaboration" class="section collaboration-band">
    <div>
      <p class="section-kicker">Collaboration</p>
      <h2>Open questions I would be happy to discuss</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="collab-list">
      <p>How can circuit foundation models represent structure, function, and physical constraints in one coherent space?</p>
      <p>How far can early-stage learning move timing, power, and reliability decisions left in the design flow?</p>
      <p>How can industrial fault simulation become faster without losing the rigor required by safety-critical chips?</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="personality" class="section compact personality">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="section-kicker">Working Style</p>
      <h2>Careful, constructive, and open to collaboration</h2>
    </div>
    <p>
      I like problems where theoretical clarity must survive contact with real tools, real circuits, and real deadlines. The thread through my work is "knowledge through action": I learn by building, measuring, refining, and sharing. I welcome collaborations on AI4EDA, 3D IC design automation, circuit representation learning, timing and power modeling, fault simulation, and hardware verification.
    </p>
  </section>

